783
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:57,200
Did he sound black, white?
Younger, older?

784
00:49:57,200 --> 00:49:58,800
High-pitched voice or low?

785
00:49:58,800 --> 00:50:01,300
He sounded, to me, like a white guy.

786
00:50:01,300 --> 00:50:04,900
Not a deep voice,
but calm, almost monotone.

787
00:50:05,700 --> 00:50:10,000
He sounded older, I would say, 40s.
Not a real young guy.

788
00:50:10,100 --> 00:50:12,700
- Can I have your notebook?
- You can't have his notes.

789
00:50:12,700 --> 00:50:16,400
As this isn't a confidential source,
we won't invoke the Maryland Shield law,

790
00:50:16,400 --> 00:50:18,500
but he'll type up a copy for you.

791
00:50:18,500 --> 00:50:21,300
But the actual document is
property of the Baltimore Sun.

792
00:50:21,400 --> 00:50:24,100
So type it up, like now.

793
00:50:24,100 --> 00:50:26,500
So, you're saying
this could be the killer?

794
00:50:27,200 --> 00:50:30,100
Can we talk off-the-record?

795
00:50:30,100 --> 00:50:33,000
The homicide unit
received a phone call this morning

796
00:50:33,100 --> 00:50:35,400
