under any circumstances.

808
00:51:12,600 --> 00:51:15,600
OK, then how do we characterize
what the police think

809
00:51:15,700 --> 00:51:18,900
- About this call to Scott?
- You can say we're...

810
00:51:18,900 --> 00:51:20,400
taking it seriously.

811
00:51:21,000 --> 00:51:24,700
Going forward, is it possible
that you would grant a one-party consent

812
00:51:24,700 --> 00:51:28,600
for us to monitor your reporter's cellphone
and office phones?

813
00:51:28,600 --> 00:51:30,600
- Absolutely not.
- I'm sorry, detective,

814
00:51:30,600 --> 00:51:33,000
but our ability to report is dependent upon

815
00:51:33,000 --> 00:51:36,600
our maintaining the confidentiality
of our conversations.

816
00:51:36,600 --> 00:51:40,600
We're perfectly willing to share
the information this individual has

817
00:51:40,600 --> 00:51:43,000
as he's definitely not a confidential source.

818
00:51:43,000 --> 00:51:45,500
But we're not going to consent
to the Baltimore Police Department

819
00:51:45,600 --> 00:51:47,300
monitoring our phones.

820
00:51:47,300 --> 00:51:50,200
- You'll tap the payphone?
- Don't print that either.

821
00:51:50,200 --> 00:51:53,300
Don't print anything
about where the killer calls from.

822
00:51:53,300 --> 00:51:54,700
He'll change up.

823
00:51:57,100 --> 00:51:59,800
Well, I'll type up my notes quick.

824
